body:
This changeset renames PyCyFunctionBinding to CyFunction and much more:

 - could be bound as method
 - support attribute assignment and __dict__ attribute
 - it could be reduced, __reduce__ method is implemented
 - __doc__, __name__ reassignment
 - could be weak referenced


Please review

comment_data.body: Using PyCFunctionObject directly allows one to ensure backwards compatibility, though I suppose this hasn't changed in 10 years.
Why not set this to NULL?
Because two versions are stored func_doc that can be set outside and (char *) one from ml
Sure, I this change is not required now, but could be useful later, I'll revert it.
The way you have it now is actually growing on me, and I think PyCFunctionObject is stable enough to leave it as is.
Regardless of the None/NULL value, I'd go through the func_doc->temp, new->func_doc, XDECREF(temp) dance here to avoid any inconsistent object state during the DECREF.

commit.message: Set binding to true for pyregr tests save/restore default directives between tests
Rename bindings into CyFunction add support for __dict__
<Py2.5 fix. define PY_WRITE_RESTRICTED if not defined
Add func_doc, func_name and func_dict aliases
cyfunction: add missed members to traverse()
Set cyfunction's func_doc attribute through temp var, thanks to Stefan
